==English==
===Etymology===
From early Middle English '''August(us)''', re-Latinized from Old English '''[[Agustus]]''' < Late Latin '''[[Agustus]]''' < Latin '''[[Augustus#Latin|Augustus]]''' (month of [[Augustus Caesar]], ''lit.'' "Venerable Caesar"), possibly from (1) Old Latin '''[[*augos]]''' (increase) < Proto-Indo-European base '''[[*aug-]]''' (to increase); or else from (2) Latin '''[[avis]]''' ("bird," ''referring to divination by observing bird flights, singing, feeding or entrails'') < Proto-Indo-European '''[[*awi-]]''' (bird); + Latin '''[[garrire]]''' (to chatter) < PIE base '''[[*gar-]]'''/'''[[*ger-]]''' ("to cry," of imitative origin).

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈɔːgəst/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"O:g@st/}}
*{{audio|en-us-August.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Proper noun===
'''August''' (''plural:'' '''[[Augusts]]''')

#The eighth [[month]] of the [[Gregorian calendar]], having 31 [[day]]s.
#:'''Last:''' [[July]]
#:'''Next:''' [[September]]
#A male or female [[given name]].
#: ''August Derleth was a science-fiction author.''

